Some of the words in the song are familiar to me because The Philippines was a former Spanish colony (1565-1898). Too bad Spanish language was abolished in The Philippines during the late 80s, only Chavacano (Spanish-creole language spoken in Zamboanga City; Cavite City, Cavite Province & Ternate, Cavite Province) still exist. Hope to revive the Spanish language in The Philippines. Some of the words in the song are the following: 

cuello (Spanish) - kuwelyo (Filipino) meaning neck, collar.

favorito (Spanish) - paborito (Filipino) meaning favorite. 

apellido (Spanish) - apelyido (Filipino) meaning last name or surname.

tiempo (Spanish) - tiyempo (Filipino) meaning time, timing.

viaje (Spanish) - biyahe (Filipino) meaning trip, travel, voyage.

salvaje (Spanish) - salbahe (Filipino) meaning wild, naughty, abusive. 

malicia (Spanish) - malisya (Filipino) meaning malice. 

pieza (Spanish) - piyesa (Filipino) meaning piece. 

lugares (plural Spanish meaning places) - mga lugar (plural Filipino meaning places) originated from Spanish singular word lugar. 

peligro (Spanish and Chavacano/Filipino) meaning danger, peril.

delicadeza (Spanish meaning delicacy/delicate) - delikadesa (Filipino meaning values)

sentido (Spanish meaning sense) - sentido (Filipino meaning temple anatomy)
